    "summary": "Vivian is a seasoned international lawyer, researcher and educator with over fifteen years of experience working for a myriad of businesses & institutions across the globe. Her broad experience ranges from acting as chair and board member to NGO\u2019s, serving as legal counsel to the private sector, teaching on universities, writing and reviewing company policies (such as whistleblower & codes of conduct) and reporting systems, to preparing and delivering training on these matters to multiple stakeholders and audiences. She is a member of the Brazilian Bar Association since 2008, a member of the Nederlandse Juristen Vereniging since 2012 and is currently in the process of qualifying with the Portuguese Bar Association. Vivian holds a Master\u2019s degree (LL.M) in Public International Law from Universiteit Leiden, a Bachelor of Laws (LL.B) from Faculdade de Direito de Sorocaba in Brazil and a Bachelor in Fine Arts (BFA) from the Gerrit Rietveld Academie in Amsterdam.\n\nNext to her legal practice, Vivian is also an artist, and passionate about envisaging and promoting a world where all human beings are free from violence and discrimination and can be respected and have a chance to participate in society on an equal footing and lead a life of dignity and opportunity. So in 2021, she co-founded Engagement Arts NL, a not-for-profit foundation that\u00a0advocates for safer working spaces within the arts in The Netherlands through public engagement, education, and research contribution, of which she still functions as a co-chair. Her unique background as a lawyer, confidential adviser and artist has invested her in researching innovative tools and practices for the prevention of coercion, discrimination & harassment in (small) communities, especially in the workspace. You can contact her for a commissioned paper, work or talk on this matter.",
